{
  "openapi": "3.0.0",
  "info": {
    "title": "ShieldNet 360 Access Platform API",
    "description": "HTTP surface for the ZTNA access platform (see docs/architecture.md).\nCovers access requests, reviews, grants, policy drafting / simulation, AI\nexplain / suggest, and inbound SCIM provisioning.\n\nThis spec is regenerated by `scripts/generate-swagger.sh` whenever a\nhandler-level change ships.\n\n## Correlation headers\n\nEvery response \u2014 including health, metrics, and error envelopes \u2014\ncarries an `X-Request-ID` header set by\n`internal/handlers.RequestIDMiddleware`. Clients SHOULD echo an inbound\n`X-Request-ID` header to thread a caller-supplied correlation key;\notherwise the server mints a UUIDv4. The same value is mirrored in the\n`request_id` field of every 4xx/5xx body (see `ErrorEnvelope`) so\nsupport tickets can be reconciled with a single key.\n",
    "version": "1.0.0"
  },
  "servers": [
    {
      "url": "/",
      "description": "Same-origin server. The access API is served by cmd/ztna-api."
    }
  ],
  "paths": {
